  <compounddef id="LOWER" kind="page">
    <compoundname>LOWER</compoundname>
    <title>LOWER$ Function</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">LOWER$(string-expression)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Converts a string expression to <bold>lower case</bold>, using standard ASCII case folding rules.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<sect3 id="LOWER_1autotoc_md614">
<title>Examples</title>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>LOWER$(&quot;HELLO&quot;)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces <computeroutput>&quot;hello&quot;</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>LOWER$(&quot;RetroRocket<sp/>123!&quot;)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces <computeroutput>&quot;retrorocket 123!&quot;</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>Normalise<sp/>case<sp/>for<sp/>comparison</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">a$<sp/>=<sp/>&quot;Yes&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">b$<sp/>=<sp/>&quot;YES&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">IF<sp/>LOWER$(a$)<sp/>=<sp/>LOWER$(b$)<sp/>THEN</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>PRINT<sp/>&quot;They<sp/>match!&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">ENDIF</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect3>
<sect3 id="LOWER_1autotoc_md616">
<title>Notes</title>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Only affects ASCII letters <computeroutput>A–Z</computeroutput> (65–90), converting them to <computeroutput>a–z</computeroutput> (97–122).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Non-alphabetic characters are unchanged.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Useful for case-insensitive comparisons, normalisation, and text processing.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
